          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1597834726622-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> and cook for 2 min, turning occasionally, then transfer them to a plate and set aside</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-low heat, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 10 min or until they're softened and caramelised</p>",
